  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We hypothesized that providing physicians treating with HIV disease, at the time of a routine
      outpatient visit, with a detailed report describing patients' adherence with HIV
      antiretroviral medications, would improve the quality of the physician-patient interaction,
      and also patients' subsequent adherence.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
